As‑shot white balance gains (R, G, B) are stored in Phocus RAW metadata.
GIOP IDT applies the inverse of these gains before the ACES matrix.

5. ISO AND SENSOR CHARACTERISTICS
  All Hasselblad medium‑format cameras use standard CMOS sensors (single
  native gain). ISO is implemented via analog gain up to ISO 6400.

  Typical for 100‑megapixel models (X2D 100C):
    Base ISO: 64
    Max analog ISO: 6400
    Read noise (base): ~2.5 e⁻
    Full well capacity: ~62,000 e⁻
    Dynamic range (SNR=1): 15.3 stops
    Peak luminance capability: 1400 nits (via HNCS HDR processing)

  The IDT for linear 16‑bit files is ISO‑agnostic; ISO affects only
  shadow noise and is metadata‑only.

6. METADATA HANDLING
  Phocus (Hasselblad RAW container, .3FR / .FFF) carries:
    - HNCS HDR active / Linear 16‑bit flag
    - Sensor calibration matrix (per‑unit)
    - White balance (Kelvin + tint)
    - Lens data (shutter / aperture)
  GIOP IDT reads these and applies the appropriate path. If no metadata
  is present, Path A (Linear 16‑bit) with identity matrix is assumed.

